commit_message:
Add retry logic for detaching device using LibVirt

Add retry logic for removing a disk device from the LibVirt
guest domain XML. This is needed because immediately after a guest
reboot, libvirtmod.virDomainDetachDeviceFlags() will silently fail
to remove the mapping from the guest domain. The async retry
behavior is done in Guest and is generic so it can be re-used by any other
detaches which hit this same race condition.

Change-Id: I983f80822a5c210929f33e1aa348a0fef91e890b
Closes-Bug: #1374508
(cherry picked from commit 6be9f2271433f9ed874b3430be2a3fe275529ebb)

Remove the get-key method here, because it brings the race.
As a result, the set_key is the same to the create_key method
as in etcd, write function is able to create or update value.

commit_message:
Resubmit the fix of race which happens in set_key of etcd

Remove the get-key method here, because it brings the race.
As a result, the set_key is the same to the create_key method
as in etcd, write function is able to create or update value.

This simple fix cannot solve the DB consistency problem. I'll
propose a blueprint to deal with it.

Change-Id: I46fd94669a74ff3e9d8e26f39de2a03cf94e7898
Closes-Bug: #1529011

commit_message:
Split DataGenerator class for v2 and v3

Currently we are working on splitting identity V2 and V3 clients
into the corresponding service clients like users_client, roles_client,
projects_client, etc. In order to do it more smoothly and simpler it was
decided to split DataGenerator class in tempest/api/identity/base.py
into the corresponding classes for Keystone V2 and V3.
So the DataGenerator class was split into three classes:
1. BaseDataGenerator. This class contains common variables and methods
   for Keystone V2 and V3 API.
2. DataGeneratorV2. This class contains specific methods for Keystone
   V2 API.
3. DataGeneratorV3. This class contains specific methods for Keystone
   V3 API.

Change-Id: I60a8d59b418d0ec24250911f449c7ed0e14ae737

commit_message:
Scenarios: remove trivial wrapper methods

These methods are harmful: they break the code-reading flow, they keep
reinventing the wheel, they give the impression we don't have consistent
names for methods, etc.

"There should be one-- and preferably only one --obvious way to do it."

Change-Id: I758f003c795b656823eb81503e6e052659b257bb

commit_message:
Add timeout property for resolving attributes

When we resolve attributes of most part of resources we make a real call
to correspoding service API and wait a response.
This patch adds new property 'attr_wait_secs', which simulates delay
during resolving attributes.
It can be used for testing huge stacks with a lot of outputs and resources.

Change-Id: I996164b6e97bb86f561b984b6bb49af6883cedc1

commit_message:
Fix bug:xrange() issue with py3.x

In python3.x, there is no method named xrange(),
it has replaced by range(),which is equal to xrange()
in python2.x. so we must fix this issue.

Closes-Bug: #1268439

Change-Id: I66f0a7f248ad77bf06e96ea7cfcb7ef5f050b13a

commit_message:
Add pagination support to the volume page

Cinder v2 supports pagination.
Added to the volumes table for both admin and project.
Also fix the Cinder REST API to handle pagination (like Glance
REST API).

To test: set 'Items Per Page' in the UI Settings page to a low number.

Co-Authored-By: Cindy Lu <clu@us.ibm.com>
Co-Authored-By: Timur Sufiev <tsufiev@mirantis.com>

Change-Id: Ib1772d6e6214dc96a09ce32fb4d9f9fb79d161f0
Closes-Bug: #1316793

commit_message:
Bring more consistency in getting l3 agents hosting router

Currently there are 2 methods to get l3 agents hosting routers:
 - list_l3_agents_hosting_router() - part of public API, returns
   l3 agents (as dicts) which are hosting specified router;
 - get_l3_agents_hosting_routers - for internal usage, returns
   l3 agents (as db objects) which are hosting specified routers,
   also accept parameters to filter by admin_state_up and active;

The issue is that it is not obvious from the name what is the difference
between the two and as a result there is no consistency in using one or
another. Also get_l3_agents_hosting_routers() is never called with more
than 1 router.

The patch renames get_l3_agents_hosting_routers to
list_db_agents_hosting_router and changes it to accept only one router
(should make query more efficient).

Partially implements blueprint improve-dvr-l3-agent-binding

Change-Id: I4f2db637d212827fbab873f6df7fbcd57fd427f6

commit_message:
Add pub-sub abstraction to Dragonflow

This adds an abstraction which allows to seperate between
the DB framework and the publish subscribe process for
DB notifications.
In this patch we use a gossip protocol framework to spread
DB changes to all the local controllers.
This opens the road for more fine grained optimization on how
we distribute control plane data.

implements blueprint: pubsub-module

Change-Id: I611e04eb880ed08c3efca296d839ac7be8dd4d47

commit_message:
include keystonev2 role assignments

This will require that user is set with project possibly being None,
otherwise we would have to query over all combinations of users and
projects to find all the assignments, which I would say is unreasonable.

project is not required by keystoneclient, but based on what I was told
by someone in #openstack-keystone, it is highly discouraged to create

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-01-25 12:56:48.000000000', 'files': ['tempest/api/orchestration/stacks/test_neutron_resources.py'], 'message': 'Replace legacy cred provider in heat api test

tempest.api.orchestration.stacks.test_neutron_resources is still using
the legacy credentials provider via
credentials_factory.ConfiguredUserManager, which relies on the
username, password, tenant_name options being set in the identity
section of the tempest config file. However those options have been
deprecated so they are not set in tempest config of devstack/gate jobs,
which results in this test raising InvalidCredentials exception in
gate-tempest-dsvm-neutron-src-python-saharaclient.
Patch replaces legacy credentials provider in test_neutron_resources
by dynamic/pre-provisioned credential provider.

Closes-Bug: #1535434
Change-Id: Ia3e751007a382563d567ecf5a6807b9928cc5948
'}]
commit_message:
Replace legacy cred provider in heat api test

tempest.api.orchestration.stacks.test_neutron_resources is still using
the legacy credentials provider via
credentials_factory.ConfiguredUserManager, which relies on the
username, password, tenant_name options being set in the identity
section of the tempest config file. However those options have been
deprecated so they are not set in tempest config of devstack/gate jobs,
which results in this test raising InvalidCredentials exception in
gate-tempest-dsvm-neutron-src-python-saharaclient.
Patch replaces legacy credentials provider in test_neutron_resources
by dynamic/pre-provisioned credential provider.

Closes-Bug: #1535434
Change-Id: Ia3e751007a382563d567ecf5a6807b9928cc5948

commit_message:
Add debug testenv in tox

Once we add debug testenv, we can use "tox -e debug" to debug test cases
when tox is running. Then tox will use oslotest which really debug our
test cases. Only we should do is insert pdb into code.It's easy to use.
This starts up the debugger pdb at the point of failure so that we can
look at the program environment, inspect variables, single step, etc.

Change-Id: I359c1101141de6462f7fc1ddb709c4dc134b5896

commit_message:
Add debug testenv in tox

Once we add debug testenv, we can use "tox -e debug" to debug test cases
when tox is running. Then tox will use oslotest which really debug our
test cases. Only we should do is insert pdb into code.It's easy to use.
This starts up the debugger pdb at the point of failure so that we can
look at the program environment, inspect variables, single step, etc.

Change-Id: I250fc3f2986cd94e80b68ec320d7df6498431211

commit_message:
Introduce new queries to return DVR routers for a host

When we remove explicit binding of dvr routers to compute nodes
we'll need a way to know which dvr routers should be returned for
a particular host in order to serve sync_routers requests from agents.
This patch adds such queries and updates l3 rpc handler to use it.

Partially implements blueprint improve-dvr-l3-agent-binding

Change-Id: I4ed4c0e50b7d261bbfd95e778a8fa2594f78e969

commit_message:
cleanup: remove infrastructure for content/type deserializer

The modular deserializer (and many other things) worked by slotting in
pluggable components based on content_type. We only support one
content type, it's json. So this is all overkill and debt now.

This first moves content type validation earlier, so that passing an
invalid content type is going to explode early. No content type, or
default text, still gets through, but we treat everything like
application/json (no real change here).

We can then delete all the selection of deserializer and action_peek
to be single instances. They are json. They will always be json. We
don't accept anything else.

A few unit tests which injected in funny places in the stack were
removed/updated to work with the new flow.

Change-Id: I2b5b08f164e0d45c55d5e2685b3e2a8641843fba

subject: Add DB transaction for df core plugin
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-30 09:30:48.000000000', 'files': ['dragonflow/neutron/plugin.py'], 'message': "Add DB transaction for df core plugin

We wrap the access to relational DB and NoSQL server into the
relational DB's transaction to prevent from data sync problem
caused by exceptions.

When plugin gets requests from API layer, it first tries to update
the relational DB to make sure the configuration is persistent.

And then plugin updates the records in distributed NoSQL server.

Finally, the transaction of relational DB is commited and the plugin
function is returned with the correct DB object.

If any exception throws in the procedure described above, the relational
DB transaction will be rolled back.

Test Case One:
Kill etcd server when operating the networks. The data is syncronized
between relational DB and etcd server.

Test Case Two:
Concurrently creates 10 network, 10 subnets, 10 routers and 10 instances
to connect to each network and 10 floating-ip allocations for each instance.
Finally, it works for all the instances to be connected via external net.

Change-Id: I36bd4133848c49ed400429c2528be99cf40e9664
Closes-Bug: #1529326
"}]
commit_message:
Add DB transaction for df core plugin

We wrap the access to relational DB and NoSQL server into the
relational DB's transaction to prevent from data sync problem
caused by exceptions.

When plugin gets requests from API layer, it first tries to update
the relational DB to make sure the configuration is persistent.

And then plugin updates the records in distributed NoSQL server.

Finally, the transaction of relational DB is commited and the plugin
function is returned with the correct DB object.

If any exception throws in the procedure described above, the relational
DB transaction will be rolled back.

Test Case One:
Kill etcd server when operating the networks. The data is syncronized
between relational DB and etcd server.

Test Case Two:
Concurrently creates 10 network, 10 subnets, 10 routers and 10 instances
to connect to each network and 10 floating-ip allocations for each instance.
Finally, it works for all the instances to be connected via external net.

Change-Id: I36bd4133848c49ed400429c2528be99cf40e9664
Closes-Bug: #1529326

commit_message:
Separate base microversion client and compute client

To support microversion in service clients, there are some
common functionality which can be shared among all projects
service client who support microversion.

This commit separates the common functionality:
- New base microversion client which can be used by any service
  client for microversion testing.

- Base compute client which will be specific to compute service
  clients.

Also adding the microversion header checking in base compute client only
as microversion implementation not yet standardize. So projects might have
different way of return microversion information in response.

Partially implements blueprint api-microversions-testing-support

Change-Id: Ic25ab63946264057f3a4365cd1ed13d9a35462db

commit_message:
Adding Monasca Driver to Datasources

Monasca is the Monitoring service for OpenStack. This patch adds
it to the list of Datasources.

Monasca supports Metrics, Measurements, Alarms and Statistics.
API calls for Metrics, Statistics and Alarms have been added
and the data represented as tables for the Congress data collection.

Measurements have been on purpose left out because it can really
flood the system.

In the future we want to have a push model integration rathen than
a poll model as implemented here.

Implements: blueprint add-monasca-datasource-driver

Change-Id: Ib8db6ba8d075798641eb21e937bc3f28135a29c0

commit_message:
Fix Subscription's queue_name variable being tuple

Because of nasty comma in the end of line of the queue_name string
variable definition, queue_name becomes a tuple with string inside,
which is wrong.

This patch fixes the problem by removing the comma.

Change-Id: Id580dfda84e4f0cb151343031d2a72ed8ef08c56
Closes-Bug: 1538367

subject: Remove unneeded glance unit test assert calls
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2016-01-26 15:59:01.000000000', 'files': ['glance/tests/unit/v1/test_upload_utils.py', 'glance/tests/unit/test_store_image.py'], 'message': 'Remove unneeded glance unit test assert calls

The glance_store library now accepts a verifier object for use with
verifying signatures, as a result of a recently merged patch [1].
There are some glance unit tests that do not expect this verifier
object to be passed to the add method of glance_store, and will
therefore fail with a new release of the glance_store library.

This patch removes the assert lines for the tests that will fail,
since it is not necessary for glance to test glance_store in that
way at the glance level.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/183110/

Change-Id: I404fbc40dafa159a63a6dfee563f05ee80c073dc
Partial-Bug: #1516031
'}]
commit_message:
Remove unneeded glance unit test assert calls

The glance_store library now accepts a verifier object for use with
verifying signatures, as a result of a recently merged patch [1].
There are some glance unit tests that do not expect this verifier
object to be passed to the add method of glance_store, and will
therefore fail with a new release of the glance_store library.

This patch removes the assert lines for the tests that will fail,
since it is not necessary for glance to test glance_store in that
way at the glance level.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/183110/

Change-Id: I404fbc40dafa159a63a6dfee563f05ee80c073dc
Partial-Bug: #1516031

commit_message:
Fix gate issues

Subscription options returned by the controller get methods was not
unserialized propertly, still containing msgpack data.

It also changes so that mongo doesn't connect before forking, and fix
uwsgi persistent connections (non) support.

Finally, it changes how keystone options are registered to use a more
robust and supported mechanism.

Conflicts:
        devstack/plugin.sh

Change-Id: I917a893c0d7175e3a465cf08c5e0375d9944fd16
(cherry picked from commit 4ba0225e1f1f3e5db19be90d689e262871737b99)

commit_message:
Add __next__() methods to utils iterators for py3

On Python 3, next(obj) calls obj.__next__(), not obj.next(). Add an
alias from __next__() to next() to be compatible with Python 2 and
Python 3.

Change-Id: Ida104d3bd7cdba557e523f18df43d56847060054

commit_message:
Add APP_COOKIE session persistence type

Neutron-LBaaS supports the APP_COOKIE session persistence type.
Neutron-LBaaS does integration tests against Octavia, including
ones which test session persistence. This patch adds APP_COOKIE
session persistence type to Octavia

commit_message:
Create dse2.DataService class

DataSerivces represents components on the DSE that expose and/or
consume data tables and RPCs.  Implementation of data table
management is left to future commits.

A DataServiceInfo class is also introduced as a container for
metadata of services running on the DSE.

Partially-implements: blueprint dist-cross-process-dse
Change-Id: Ide2fc80107b303265cff5c46889d24123b80c1c4

commit_message:
Clean up horizon.scss

A major part of the css reorg is a better organization of the css
styles themselves.

horizon.scss should be a global import level file.  This file
should not contain any styles, as it tends to just become a catch
all for ALL styles.

Great care has been taken to divide up or remove ALL of the styles
from horizon.scss

Several new files have been added to aid in organization and the
css reorg effort going forward:

 * _contrib.scss: Styles that currently relate to a contrib page
   -> These should be moved out eventually to the contrib area

 * _debt.scss: Styles that need to be researched and/or removed
   -> Its difficult to tell at this time if they are still used

 * _legacy.scss: Styles that have legacy value only

 * _hacks.scss: Every css project needs it.  Usually when something
                hackish was really required. I.E., usage of
                !important, etc

Partially-Implements: blueprint horizon-theme-css-reorg
Change-Id: I7eb0f8e670d31b547c084b0cb2ea334c290d7246

commit_message:
Allow certain command line arguments to be passed from file

This commit allows the use of a .bandit file, which will be in
the ini format and used to pass command line arguments.  This is
useful for multiple projects which are running in the same gate,
want to be able to exclude different files per-project, and
aren't using tox.

Change-Id: I4256bdb7df2416f3cc01798882fb7e2e229790a3

commit_message:
Pass attachment_id to Cinder when detach a volume

Cinder needs the attachment_id to properly identify which attachment
of a volume to detach. This patch adapts the Cinder driver to pass
the required information. The attachment_id is necessary for volumes
that enable multiple attachments in order to terminate the connection
properly. The attachment_id is retrieved in the API layer where
available and sent through RPC, the RPC version is bumped to 4.7.

Also the translation functions are modified to retrieve all necessary
information for the volume info coming from Cinder including the multiple
attachments. The Nova API returns the volume info in the same format
as earlier.

Co-Authored-By: Ildiko Vancsa <ildiko.vancsa@ericsson.com>

Partially-implements: blueprint multi-attach-volume
Change-Id: I3cdc49924acbdd21d1e6678a3bb4cf7de7f1db1a
